{% extends "base.html.jinja2" %}
{% block heading %}
    <h1 class="display-4">LISTENING TEST</h1>
    <hr class="my-4">
    <p>
        Welcome, and thank you for participating in this listening test.
        <p>
        <br>
        <br>
        INSTRUCTIONS:
        <p>
        Try to rank sounds based on the delivery rate, and style rather than on audio quality.
        <p>
        For example, something that sounds like a baseball announcer but with static (e.g. interference over a car radio) should be considered in the 4 or 5 (natural delivery) categories. If the audio quality is so bad it interferes with your listening, it can be ok to score lower however.
        <p>
        A clearly voice with unnatural delivery but perfect, crystal clear audio quality should be considered more in the 3, 2, or 1 categories - unless the timing and style feels "natural" to you (then it can be scored higher).
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
        <p>
        Rate each example as independently as possible, some of the sentences may be duplicates but try to rate separately without doing direct "head-to-head" comparison.
        <p>
        There will be a total of 21 questions - scroll down to see the audio player, and begin.
        <p>
        Thank you again for participating!
    </p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>
        Rating system for this test, and approximate description of the score for each value
        <ul>
            <li>5 (Natural delivery)</li>
            <li>4 (Somewhat natural)</li>
            <li>3 (Acceptable/Neutral)</li>
            <li>2 (Somewhat unnatural)</li>
            <li>1 (Very unnatural)</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
{% endblock %}
{% block form_questions %}
    {% for question in questions %}
        <div class="card form-group" style="{{ question.style }}">
            <div class="card-header">{{ question.title }}</div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    <audio controls src="{{ question.audio_path }}">
                        Your browser does not support the audio element.
                    </audio>
                </p>
                <div class="form-check">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="{{ question.name }}" id="{{ question.name }}_1" value="5" required>
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="{{ question.name }}_1">5 (Natural delivery)</label>
                </div>
                <div class="form-check">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="{{ question.name }}" id="{{ question.name }}_2" value="4" required>
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="{{ question.name }}_2">4 (Somewhat natural)</label>
                </div>
                <div class="form-check">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="{{ question.name }}" id="{{ question.name }}_3" value="3" required>
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="{{ question.name }}_3">3 (Acceptable/Neutral)</label>
                </div>
                <div class="form-check">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="{{ question.name }}" id="{{ question.name }}_4" value="2" required>
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="{{ question.name }}_4">2 (Somewhat unnatural)</label>
                </div>
                <div class="form-check">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="{{ question.name }}" id="{{ question.name }}_5" value="1" required>
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="{{ question.name }}_5">1 (Very unnatural)</label>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    {% endfor %}
{% endblock %}
